$interpreted: Fatima: Darn it, thought they would drop off the hostages halfway. Did they still choose to bring the brats into the isolation village?
Fatima: If that's the case, things are going to get tricky...
Elio: Miss Fatima, what is this isolation village?
Fatima: Panthers who violated the ancestors' rules will be taken to a separate village for them to reflect on their mistakes.
Fatima: Only after they repent their wrong-doings will they then be allowed to return to the Panther tribe.
Elio: So, in human terms, a "prison" more or less?
Elio: Wait, then if Sis Annie and others are taken to that place, isn't that extremely dangerous for them?
Fatima: That's why we have to hurry and get them out of there! The isolation village is right ahead...
Panther Traitor: Hahaha, sorry about that!
Panther Traitor: Even though you helped us escape, boss Jerus said that he can't trust someone that is willing to help traitors~ So... time for you to die!
Fooled Warrior: H, HELP!
Fatima: Damnit!

Fooled Warrior: Fatima... I, I'm so sorry... Jerus tricked me.
He told to bring human items into the tribe...
Fooled Warrior: He never said that those things will explode... All the other Panthers are...
Elio: Did you see the three Rune Academy girls?
Fooled Warrior: ... When Jerus saw those three, he feared that Rune Academy will interfere again. So he left them in the village before he escaped...
Elio: Miss Fatima, I'm going with you too!
Fatima: I can't get you guys involved in this mess anymore!

Fatima: You help me treat his injuries first.
I'll be right back as soon as I rescue the three brats!
Elio: Understood. Please be careful!
Fatima: Untied the ropes...
Fatima: Hey! Are you girls alright?
Annie: ... Miss... Fatima?
Betty: ... Where are we...?
Fatima: Good to see that you're all fine. Let's go!
Cara: What is this!?
Fatima: Crap, it's a trap!

Elio: That direction... isn't that where Miss Fatima went?
What is happening!?
Jerus: Hehe, looks like I finally had my revenge!
Elio: Revenge...
Elio: Could it be... that you're the Jerus Miss Fatima mentioned? What did you do to them!?
Jerus: When I saw those three dumb girls, and I heard that Fatima was with them, I immediately knew that she will most certainly come to rescue these students.
Jerus: Therefore, I left Fatima a small "gift" by making a trap with the remaining gunpowder I used to attack the guards...
Elio: You bastard... You had plenty of time to run. Why would you purposely throw that away to do such an atrocity!
Jerus: It was her and Charle who took everything from me, to begin with. In return, I have to make her taste my sufferings as well!
Elio: Damnit!
Jerus: Give up! A bookworm like you is no match for me!
Elio: In your dreams!... Can't be bogged down here by you any longer... I still have to go save them...
Jerus: Save them? You really think that I, who wanted Fatima dead more than anything else, would even leave her a chance to survive?

Jerus: The amount of gunpowder I used is not going to just leave a mark. 
Bet they are all in pieces by now!

Elio: ... We finally became friends...
... How dare you killed them...
Elio: Damnit, Damnit...
Jerus: Hmph, too scared to move?
Jerus: DIE!
Jerus: What!?
Elio: ... You despicable piece of scum... I'm going to kill you right here!
Elio: ARGHHHH!!
